olive oil
2 potato
1 stalk celery
1 packet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 packet Japanese Dressing
drizzle vinegar (rice wine or white wine)
1 packet mayonnaise

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into fries, then place on a lined oven
tray.
• Season with salt and drizzle with olive oil.
Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until
tender, 20-25 minutes.

Little cooks: Kids can help toss the fries.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice celery.

• In a medium bowl, combine sweet soy
seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil. Add pork
loin steaks and turn to coat.

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat
with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook
pork until cooked through, 3-4 minutes each
side (depending on thickness).
• Remove pan from heat, add sweet chilli sauce
and turn pork to coat.

• In a second medium bowl, combine shredded
cabbage mix, celery, Japanese dressing and a
drizzle of vinegar. Season to taste.

Little cooks: Help combine the ingredients for the
slaw!

• Slice the pork.
• Divide fries, celery slaw and sweet chilli-glazed
pork between plates.
• Serve with mayonnaise. Enjoy!